cy predictor to stabilize performance across varying sparsity levels, ensuring robustness even when aggressive pruning is applied. This results in faster convergence to correct sentence pairs with fewer false positives, improving both throughput and precision.\n\nThe impact of this work lies in enabling scalable, real-time parallel corpus construction for low-resource languages, where large candidate sets make exact search prohibitive. By shifting from reactive (post-expansion) to proactive (pre-expansion) pruning grounded in predictive modeling, CAPE opens a new direction in efficient constrained decoding applicable beyond retrieval—e.g., controlled generation, grammar-guided synthesis, and interactive translation.",
